JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 281
EP  - 293
VL  - 9
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Standards certainly contribute to the success of human endeavors. But standards also can contribute to the stagnation of ideas, technologies, and organizations. These two aspects of standards will he illustrated by investigating three types of standards: (1) culturally determined standards, such as the norms of behavior of scientists, (2) standards as measures of progress for evaluating innovations, and (3) quantitative performance standards, for example, worktime standards.
AB  - Standards certainly contribute to the success of human endeavors. But standards also can contribute to the stagnation of ideas, technologies, and organizations. These two aspects of standards will he illustrated by investigating three types of standards: (1) culturally determined standards, such as the norms of behavior of scientists, (2) standards as measures of progress for evaluating innovations, and (3) quantitative performance standards, for example, worktime standards.
