N2  - Research utilizing computer models to study human cognitive and social processes is noteworthy because of its quality, quantity, and rate of growth. It has influenced both research methodology and the body of knowledge in the behavioral sciences. The close relationship between management and the behavioral sciences implies that such research will probably affect management thought.
